Umm an mcp server for making fastapi endpoints usable by models
(experimenting)

## Run

- API server: `uvicorn api:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000`
- MCP stdio server: `python server.py`
- Demo client: `python client.py`

## Tests

Run all tests:

`python -m unittest discover -s tests -v`

## Demo target API for MCP

Run a small FastAPI app from `tests/` that MCP can discover:

`uvicorn demo_target_api:app --app-dir tests --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8001`

Use this base URL in MCP tools:

`http://127.0.0.1:8001`

Example direct checks:

- `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8001/health`
- `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8001/openapi.json`
